Type: Package
Package: RGISTools
Title: Tools for Downloading, Processing, and Smoothing Time Series of Satellite Images From Landsat, Modis, and Sentinel
Version: 0.9.2
Author: U PÃ©rez - Goya [aut, cre] <unai.perez@unavarra.es>,
        A F Militino [aut] <militino@unavarra.es>,
        M D Ugarte [aut] <lola@unavarra.es>,
        M Montesino - SanMartin [aut] <manuel.montesino@unavarra.es>
Maintainer: U Perez - Goya <unai.perez@unavarra.es>
Description: Downloading, processing, and smoothing time series of satellite images in a region of interest. RGISTools functions allow a unified access to multispectral images from Landsat, Modis and Sentinel repositories. RGISTools  also offers capabilities for processing satellite images, including tile mosaicking, cropping and extracting the variables of interest. Finally, the package implements the genSmoothingIMA and genSmoothingCovIMA functions for gap-filling time series of images.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), raster, gdalUtils, sp
Imports: Rdpack, XML, xml2, utils, fields, magick, urltools, rjson, rvest, tools,  methods, curl 
RdMacros: Rdpack
